## 4. The Hand Feel Experience

- Impact Sensation
    - Hardness Words: Firm, dense, and solid. Feels exactly like a true 50-degree ESN (approx 38-39 degree DHS).
    - Feedback: Very clear. The white sponge transmits vibrations cleanly to the handle, letting you know exactly where you struck the ball.
    - Hold vs. Release: Hold-dominant. It grabs the ball for a noticeably long time before releasing it dynamically.
    - Dwell Time: High. The grip of the top sheet extends the feeling of the ball sinking into the rubber.

- Sound/Click
    - Moderate click. It produces a satisfying, sharp sound on full power loops, but it does not have the loud, metallic Tensor crack of older, softer rubbers.

